President Trump expressed his support for Scott Pruitt, the head of the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA), stating that he has done a fantastic job and has been courageous. When asked about the reports concerning Pruitt, the President said he will look into it closely but believes that Pruitt is a good man. Trump also mentioned that he wants to have 2,000 to 4,000 National Guard troops at the border and is considering the cost. He discussed the issue of Amazon, stating that they are not on an even playing field and that he will study the situation to ensure a level playing field for all businesses. When asked about the $130,000 payment to Stormy Daniels, Trump said he did not know about it and suggested asking his attorney, Michael Cohen. He reiterated his support for Pruitt and mentioned that he is loved by people in coal and energy country.